<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Female.</emphasis>
Body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3A</figureCitation>
) moderately stout, dorsoventrally flattened. Body length 1.10 mm in dissected and figured specimen (1.22 mm in holotype). Prosome 680 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
555 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, ~ 56% as long as body length. Posterolateral corners of all prosomal somites pointed or angular. Urosome (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3B</figureCitation>
) five-segmented. Fifth pedigerous somite 234 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
wide, slightly wider than genital double-somite. Genital double-somite subcircular, flattened ventrally, thin laterally, slightly wider than long (220 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
227 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) in dissected specimen or slightly longer than wide in smaller other specimens; lateral margin with small denticle (this denticle absent smaller specimens) as indicated by arrowhead in Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3B</figureCitation>
; genital apertures positioned dorsolaterally at anterior part of double-somite. Three abdominal somites 84 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
136 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, 61 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
127 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, and 45 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
114 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, respectively. Genital double-somite and first two free abdominal somites with membranous fringe along posterior margin. Anal somite with row of spinules along posteroventral margin. Caudal ramus (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3C</figureCitation>
) short, 1.15 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide (55 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
48 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
), slightly longer than anal somite, armed with six setae (setae II-VII), and ornamented with setules on distal half of inner margin and fine spinules along posteroventral margin; seta II (outer lateral seta) positioned at midlength of ramus, spiniform in proximal half but setiform in distal half; seta III (outer distal seta) also proximally spiniform and distally setiform; dorsal seta (seta VII) annulated proximally; setae II, III, and VII naked, but other three setae pinnate.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 3" startId="F3">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lee &amp; Chang &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2022" class="Hexanauplia" family="Clausidiidae" genus="Hemicyclops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemicyclops rapax" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hemicyclops rapax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
habitus, dorsal 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C</emphasis>
anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D</emphasis>
antennule 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E</emphasis>
antenna 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">F</emphasis>
mandible 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">G</emphasis>
paragnath 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">H</emphasis>
maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A</emphasis>
); 0.1 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B</emphasis>
); 0.05 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">C, D</emphasis>
); 0.02 mm (
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E-H</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rostrum small, with convex posterior margin. Antennule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3D</figureCitation>
) 237 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
long, seven-segmented; armature formula 4, 14, 6, 3, 4+aesthetasc, 2+aesthetasc, and 7+aesthetasc; first segment ornamented with fines setules on anterior surface; setae and aesthetascs slender; most setae naked except single on each fourth and fifth segments and three on terminal segment. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3E</figureCitation>
) consisting of coxa, basis and three-segmented endopod; armature formula 0, 1, 1, 4, and 7; basis ornamented with two patches of spinules on inner margin and several setules on outer margin; first endopodal segment with acutely pointed outer distal corner and patch of spinules on inner surface and patch of small spinules at inner distal corner; second endopodal segment with prominent inner distal prolongation (this prolongation distinctly longer than wide; its two apical setae strong, claw-like), ornamented with broad spinules along inner margin and row of small spinules near outer distal corner; third endopodal segment as long as wide, ornamented with two rows of minute setules on outer side; four of seven setae on third endopodal segment claw-like, wrinkled in middle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Labrum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4A</figureCitation>
) with denticles and spinules on posterior margin. Labium (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4B</figureCitation>
) denticulated along anterior margin, spinulose subapically. Mandible (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3F</figureCitation>
) distally armed with one stout, denticulate element, one spinulose, plate-like element and two pinnate setae. Paragnath (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3G</figureCitation>
) lobate, ornamented with fine setules on middle and subdistal regions and spinules on distal region, with trace of articulation subdistally. Maxillule (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A habitus, dorsal B urosome, dorsal (arrowhead indicates a small denticle on lateral margin of genital double-somite) C anal somite and caudal rami, dorsal D antennule E antenna F mandible G paragnath H maxillule. Scale bars: 0.2 mm (A); 0.1 mm (B); 0.05 mm (C, D); 0.02 mm (E-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720723" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">3H</figureCitation>
) unequally bilobed distally; smaller inner lobe armed with three weakly pinnate setae; larger outer lobe with five pinnate setae. Maxilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4C</figureCitation>
) two-segmented; proximal segment (syncoxa) armed with three setae, smallest one setule-like, inserted on proximal region of spiniform largest seta, and ornamented with row of minute spinules on proximal region; distal segment (basis) distally armed with three heavily spinulose or denticulate spines and single seta. Maxilliped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A maxilliped B distal part of maxilliped C leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A, B); 0.05 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720725" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5A</figureCitation>
) four-segmented; first segment (syncoxa) with two large setae on inner margin; second segment (basis) also with two large setae on inner margin; third segment (first endopodal segment) short, unarmed; terminal segment (second endopodal segment) forming large hook (this hook much longer than proximal three segments), proximally armed with one spine bearing seven spinules on outer margin and four small, naked setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A maxilliped B distal part of maxilliped C leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A, B); 0.05 mm (C)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720725" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">5B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 4" startId="F4">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Figure 4.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lee &amp; Chang &amp; Kim" authorityYear="2022" class="Hexanauplia" family="Clausidiidae" genus="Hemicyclops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hemicyclops rapax" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rapax">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Hemicyclops rapax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., female 
