<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Legs 1-4 biramous, with three-segmented rami (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4D-F</figureCitation>
); basis spinulose along outer margin and posterior margin between bases of rami. Intercoxal plate setulose in leg 1 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4D</figureCitation>
) but spinulose in legs 2-4 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Hemicyclops rapax sp. nov., female A labrum B labium C maxilla D leg 1 E leg 2 F leg 4. Scale bars: 0.02 mm (A-C); 0.05 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1115.83266.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/720724" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">4E, F</figureCitation>
). Outer spines on exopod of leg 1 tipped with setule. Leg 3 armed and shaped as leg 2. Two inner setae on third endopodal segment of leg 4 stiff, spiniform. Armature formula for legs 1-4 as follows:
</paragraph>
